company_description:
We are developing a platform that allows anyone to easily fine-tune small language model (SLMs). 
How easily? Imagine writing an in-context learning prompt to an LLM with a few dozen examples.

Such specialized SLMs can solve specific tasks at much lower latency and cost than generic, pre-trained LLMs while maintaining accuracy. Additionally their small size allow for local deployment – leveraging the benefits of CPU inference (speed, cost, security, networking, reduced dependencies).

Our hypothesis is that such small models will be the building blocks of highly performant multi-agentic AI products of the future.

company_description:
AI is advancing fast. The tools to create AI deepfakes and AI-supported fraud are no longer reserved for experts. They’re accessible to everyone: fast, scalable, and frighteningly good. What once took teams now takes minutes. The threat is real. 

LAYONARDO builds the defense: we develop LND DEEP, a multi-indicator deepfake- and fraud-detection system. Our proprietary agentic AI, called Deep Visual Analytics (DVA), orchestrates specialized, custom-trained detectors across visual, structural, semantic, textual, and metadata forensics. It reasons over their outputs and resolves contradictions to produce a single, explainable, accurate risk score.

LAYONARDO helps banks, insurers, logistics platforms, and universities reduce fraud as well as legal, regulatory, and reputational risk. We’ve validated our MVP with early pilots in banking, higher education, and transportation. Now we are raising a €3 million seed round to scale across Europe and the US in a multi-billion-billion euro market.
prominent_investors: Markus Guttenberg, Hubert Deutsch, Pfeiffer HandelsgmbH
shortDescription: LAYONARDO develops software that detects AI-generated deepfakes and visual AI content to combat fraud and protect ethical standards and copyrights.
